1. Introduction
We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how the Pro Math - Photo Math Scanner app collects, uses, and safeguards your data.

2. Data We Collect
Our app may collect the following types of data:

User-Provided Data:

Images: Photos you provide for solving math problems.
Automatically Collected Data:

Device Information: Information such as device type, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Data: Information about how you use the app, including interactions and session durations.
Third-Party Services:

AdMob (Google Ads): For displaying advertisements. AdMob may collect:
Device Identifiers (e.g., Advertising ID).
IP Address.
App Usage Data.
Google Analytics: For analyzing app performance. Google Analytics may collect:
App Interaction Data.
Crash Reports.
Device and Network Data.
For more information on how these services collect and use data, please refer to:

AdMob Privacy Policy
Google Analytics Privacy Policy
3. How We Use Your Data
We use the collected data to:

Provide and Improve the App: Enhance features, fix bugs, and optimize performance.
Display Ads: Serve personalized and non-personalized advertisements through AdMob.
Analyze Usage: Understand how users interact with the app to improve functionality.
4. Data Sharing
We do not share your personal data with third parties, except in the following cases:

With Service Providers: Such as AdMob and Google Analytics, to facilitate app services.
Legal Requirements: If required by law, we may share data with government or law enforcement authorities.
Business Transfers: In case of mergers, acquisitions, or asset sales.
5. Data Security
We take reasonable steps to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure.

6. User Rights
You have the right to:

Access and Review Your Data: Request a copy of the data we hold.
Delete Your Data: Request data deletion, where applicable.
Opt-Out of Personalized Ads: Through your device settings or via the appâ€™s ad settings.
7. Children's Privacy
Our app is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe your child has provided us with personal data, please contact us.

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the updated effective date. Please review it periodically.

